{\plain \fs26 \fs26 }{\plain \fs26 \ul\fs26 (a)  The General Assembly finds and declares that the strong public policy of this state is \softline
in favor of open government; that open government is essential to a free, open, and \softline
democratic society; and that public access to public records should be encouraged to foster \softline
confidence in government and so that the public can evaluate the expenditure of public \softline
funds and the efficient and proper functioning of its institutions.  The General Assembly 
further finds and declares that there is a strong presumption that public records should be \softline
made available for public inspection without delay.  This article shall be broadly construed \softline
to allow the inspection of governmental records.  The exceptions set forth in this article, \softline
together with any other exception located elsewhere in the Code, shall be interpreted \softline
narrowly to exclude only those portions of records addressed by such exception.}{\plain \fs26 \fs26 \par
